<p>GDP growth: 4.2% GDP: $381bn (PPP: $663bn) Inflation: 3.2% Population: 68.8m GDP per head: $5,540 (PPP: $9,630)</p>

<p>The influence of a populist billionaire, Thaksin Shinawatra, established with his first election victory in 2001, was barely diminished by his ouster in a 2006 coup, and is now waxing once more. The rise of his sister, Yingluck Shinawatra, to the prime ministership following a landslide for her Puea Thai party in 2011 appears to signal the rehabilitation of his policies, if not of the man himself. Policy, security and the tenor of daily life will reflect the long face-off between the Shinawatra camp and the royalist establishment. The prospect of political turmoil weighs on the economic outlook, but growth is likely to stay healthy.</p>

